                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">-	The title of the work, መ/መነኰሳት, is written on a slip of paper stuck to the front board. &#xD;
-	A word ተአም[ር] is written, in black paint, on the front board. It probably refers to the content of the ms. from which the board originates. &#xD;
-	Omitted letters or words written interlineally, occasionally over erasures: fols. 5va, 10rb, 18ra, 20ra, 21ra, 21rb, 22vb, 25va, 31va, 41ra, 42ra, 42vb, 50r, 59rb, 62rb.&#xD;
-	Erasures: 22vb, 24r, 37va. &#xD;
-	Corrections over erasures: 40ra, 47ra.&#xD;
-	Cues for the rubricator: fols. 10v, 11r, 12r, 14r, 27r, 28r.&#xD;
-	Names erased from fols. 11vb, 12ra. &#xD;
-	An extensive note erased from fol. 71r. &#xD;
-	Minor notes, writing exercises (in Ethiopic syllabary), doodles: fols. 1rv, 2r, 34r, 43r, 45vb, 68v.</item>
                     </list>
